cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.SY, cs.LG 

The paper presents algorithms for efficient dot product and matrix multiplication in arbitrary-precision floating-point and ball arithmetic. This involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS) for handling large matrices. The paper also mentions the use of linear algebra (cs.SC) and polynomial operations, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
